Package ohos.event.intentagent

Class IntentAgentHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.intentagent.IntentAgentHelper

  • public final class IntentAgentHelper
extends Object
    A helper class used to obtain, trigger, cancel, and compare IntentAgent objects and to obtain the bundle name, UID, and hash code value of an IntentAgent object.

    The methods provided by this class are all static and can be called without creating an object of this class.

    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Notification#ANS

    • Method Detail

      • getIntentAgent

        public static IntentAgent getIntentAgent​(Context context,
                                         IntentAgentInfo paramsInfo)
        Obtains an IntentAgent object.

        The IntentAgent class does not have any constructor, and you can only use this method to create an IntentAgent object.

        Parameters:
        context - Indicates the context of the caller. This parameter cannot be null.
        paramsInfo - Indicates the IntentAgentInfo object that contains parameters of the IntentAgent object to create.
        Returns:
        Returns the created IntentAgent object.
        Since:
        3

      • triggerIntentAgent

        public static void triggerIntentAgent​(Context context,
                                      IntentAgent agent,
                                      IntentAgent.OnCompleted onCompleted,
                                      EventHandler handler,
                                      TriggerInfo paramsInfo)
        Triggers an IntentAgent.

        After this method is called, events associated with the specified IntentAgent will be executed, such as starting an ability or sending a common event.

        Parameters:
        context - Indicates the context of the caller. This parameter cannot be null.
        agent - Indicates the IntentAgent to trigger.
        onCompleted - Indicates the callback method to be called after the IntentAgent is triggered. This parameter can be null.
        handler - Indicates the thread for executing the callback indicated by onCompleted. If this parameter is null, the callback method will be executed in a thread in the thread pool of the current process.
        paramsInfo - Indicates the TriggerInfo object that contains triggering parameters.
        Since:
        3

      • cancel

        public static void cancel​(IntentAgent agent)
        Cancels an IntentAgent.

        Only the application that creates the IntentAgent can cancel it.

        Parameters:
        agent - Indicates the IntentAgent to cancel.
